  <T n="name">0x448D8BD0<!--String: "Swordsmanship Duels"--></T>
  <L n="slides">
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP21\UI\Tutorial\EP21_Lessons_Duels1.png">2f7d0004:00000000:a84855c4aed4f174</T>
      <T n="text">0x539779E1<!--String: "Trying to get ahead without the hard work? Sims can hone their <b><font color='#199C2C'>Swordsmanship skill</font></b> to get ahead in other aspects of their life!\n\nAt <b><font color='#199C2C'>Swordsmanship level 5</font></b>, a Sim can challenge their <b><font color='#199C2C'>Dynasty's Head</font></b> for their position regardless of rank or status within the <b><font color='#199C2C'>Dynasty</font></b>.\nJust hope that your Sim's skills are high enough or it could backfire.\n\nLevel 6 allows Noble Sims to deal with their <b><font color='#199C2C'>Noble Rival</font></b> honorably through a duel and level 7 allows Sims to challenge senior colleagues in any career for that <b><font color='#199C2C'>promotion</font></b> they've had their eye on!"--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP21\UI\Tutorial\EP21_Lessons_Duels2.png">2f7d0004:00000000:a84855c4aed4f177</T>
      <T n="text">0x4CD96FC0<!--String: "At level 3 of the Swordsmanship skill a Sim can challenge another to a <b><font color='#199C2C'>Duel for Another Sim's Heart</font></b> if they are competing for the affection of the same Sim. Will your Sim prove their intent or embarrass themselves in front of their love?\n\nWhat if your Sim is more successful in love, and engaged to their beloved? At level 4 a Sim can Duel a Parent or Dynasty Head of their betrothed to gain their <b><font color='#199C2C'>Permission to Marry</font></b>."--></T>
    </U>
  </L>
